txt1: The following description is about the project management process. It starts with making an introduction.  Once making an introduction occurs, the process is split into 3 parallel branches: getting approval, recording the basic idea and identifying the approval status.  Once getting approval occurs, working out its value needs to be done.  Once all pre-tasks are executed, then laying out a timeline should be done.  After laying out a timeline, you need to have a kickoff meeting. When having a kickoff meeting is completed, the process is split into 2 parallel branches: keeping communication and recording KPIs.  Once all pre-tasks are executed, then one or more of the following paths should be executed: evaluating project outcomes, ensuring the project is completed.  The process is now completed.
